cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR

This paper involves computer vision techniques and deep learning networks to estimate the localization information of a vehicle using monocular camera systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with intelligent transportation systems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The use of deep learning networks for fine-grained vehicle model classification indicates that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the development of an algorithm, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with surveillance camera systems, which could suggest that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
